<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171717">My Gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aquaminismallwater>Aquamini Smallwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(2/14/03 7:41:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   yes</span><hr size=1> yes try PoV group in caves brings great exp. the WL area is constant pulls. bring a horse if you plan to hunt there. standing up medding helps and if a train comes, just run as fast as you can DONT LOOK BACK NEO.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vilephire>Vilephire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/03 5:44:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: yes</span><hr size=1> I have always disliked Plane of Valor, and that dislike has only grown since the zone now hosts 80ish people during prime time. If you find it hard to get groups in Valor, or just dislike the zone, then head to Plane of Storms. Unlike groups in PoV, most of the time groups in PoS tend to improvise. Meaning you can start exp grinding right away instead of waiting on &lt;insert 'important' class here&gt; to join the group. I have duo'd sucessfully in Plane of Storms with the following classes: Druid, Magician, Ranger, Shadowknight, Shaman, and Wizard. Its easy to get exp regardless of your class make up. If you only have a snarer, go agro kite the frogs (they do not summon, very easy and safe exp.) If you have someone who can slow, go to the Desert and just kill trash mobs, very easy, just make sure you avoid adds on pulls (which is not hard to do, but pathing here does take some getting used to.) If you have another pet class, go basically anywhere. Just send pets in, and either back pet out and heal it when low, or cast a new one when yours dies.<br>
<br>
While in Plane of Storms, try to find some groups doing giants. Pick up the pieces needed for the Bastion of Thunder flag, and that will open up another very nice alternative exp spot for you. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mfpd.net/bgreer/vilephire.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Vilephire Marisol Epeche</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Arch Mage of Arete, Eci</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 387<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/03 11:29:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: yes</span><hr size=1> mage+slower duo can easily handle the storms wandering mobs, too. Be warned: they enrage so either have pet hold or be prepared to spam back off <p>------------<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=433620">Kranken</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Convoker<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Xev<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->&quot;Where's my pet..?&quot;</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A> at: 2/17/03 11:29:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilmir123>Kilmir123</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.lowlandelites.net/vb/avatar.php?userid=13&dateline=1034772585" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/03 3:30:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: yes</span><hr size=1> 2 mages + 1 chanter in PoS. We went through the wildlife at the forest (trees, frogs, bears, snakes) like wildfire.<br>
<br>
Enrage surpassing by dropping 2 firebolts and a chanter nuke when the mob is anywhere between 10 and 20%.<br>
<br>
Only problem was that we had some downtime because of a Winged Death on the person who pulled the last casting tree.<br>
We fixed that later on by adding a necro.<br>
<br>
Desert should be doable, we might try that next time as well. Giants are not good to be single pulled and the chanter has problems mezzing them (the ones that CAN be mezzed at all). <p>Arch Convoker Rhand Drago'Magica<br>
